                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d447">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/4356: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName corresp="#p_JNT1" type="from"
                            >Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-02-22T14:00:00+08:00"
                            >February 22, 1932—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received February 22—7:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Rumors of despatch of Japanese reenforcements are becoming persistent. I hope
                    that the Department will find it possible to instruct Embassy at Tokyo to
                    express when reenforcements are sent they will not be landed inside Settlement
                    area.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_JNT1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
